title: Qld mum missing after school drop off - 9news.com.au
text:
Qld mum missing after school drop off By AAP 
A young mother has gone missing in central Queensland after dropping her child off at school on Monday morning. 
Police say 25-year-old Hannah Cook was last seen in the Gladstone CBD around 9am on Monday driving a black Mitsubishi ASX wagon with Queensland license plates 282 WSI. 
She is described as around 172cm tall, with a slim build, long dark brown hair and brown eyes.
